subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen black with light grey pruinescence, covered with distinct setae. Sternites lighter than tergites, except sternite 5 black and with median-apical protuberance (
Fig. 19
). Sternites 6 and 7 with sclerotized areas. Tergite 8 narrow; sternite 8 large.

Terminalia (
Fig. 19
). Epandrium subtriangular; cercus with many setae and apparently with very robust apical setae (broken); hypandrium membranous distally, joined to subtriangular protuberance by narrow sclerotized arch; ejaculatory apodeme flattened laterally (
Fig. 21
); phallus rather transparent distally with two ducts (
Fig. 20
).
